events.body:
> Each `/headers/block` is a unique resource, so I think it makes sense to keep the block hash as part of the URI path.

@jnewbery this endpoint returns a list of `count` headers, not the unique resource.

```
// list of headers
GET /rest/headers?block_hash=&count=&format=

VS

// an header
GET /rest/headers/block_hash?format=
```

Anyway, just wanted to note my opinion, I'm fine with block hash in the path.

